rComments: My least favourite English professor. He doesn't come to class with anything prepared (most of the time it looks like he's just winging it). Lectures were basically one big tutorial and he doesn't post anything online. Marking was extremely hard. I got As on all my essay components, yet finished with a B-. The whole class was just sloppy.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Participation matters', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: I rated him before for ENG201, he was incredible in that class, but in this class, he seemed disengaged and rude.  I went to him in office hours, and he used something I said to lower my grade on the final essay.   I'm very disappointed because I was looking forward to this class.

I took ENG201 as a requirement, but ended up loving the course.  Brent is amazing in lectures and is able to span from history to literature.  He gives plenty of opportunities to help his students.  In order to do well, participate!! if you're quiet, don't take it.  Make sure you follow his instructions, and you're bound to do well. Also, omg hot

My fav prof of all time. He wasn't at first, I didn't really "get" him and thought he was too tough but the work I produced in his classes is the best work I've ever done. He's really nice and helpful (he edited a single essay over and over again and talked it through with me) and expects the best from his students. Don't be afraid, he's awesome!

This prof inspired me to take English as a specialist instead of science. He is tough, but its only to challenge and push you to do your best. He can read through your bs, but he helps you every step of the way to do well. Just show up for office hours and be nice!

He can come off a little odd at first, but he's been one of the best profs I have had the privilege to study under. If you attend office hours, it will save your grade. He'll know you are trying and sometimes will raise your grade if he feels you deserve it. Extremely entertaining lectures. He draws from all media forms to analyze lit. Loved it!

He's an odd character, who marks quite low, even if you show up to many office hours and helps you with everything. As a student with a good GPA, I felt close to stupid in his class. His essays are humungous, and he's not afraid to fully tell you to drop his course (over and over again) if you are not doing well.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Tough grader', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: Beware!!! This class, well more like this professor makes you want to rethink everything in life, like your entire existence. He believes he knows everything and its not YOUR interpretation, its HIS interpretation that matters. Poetry shouldn't be this hard, but he makes it like rocket science. If you want to live, DO NOT TAKE ANY CLASSES WITH HIM!

He's the reason I am continuing to pursue my English degree. You may find him hard but if you approach him for help he will remember you and trust me it will make all the difference. He's super nice and crazy interesting. Attend class because I structured all my essays based on class discussions and did well. Definitely taking more of his classes.

Great prof!  He made every class interesting and enjoyable (English soon became my favourite course).  You have to work hard on your essays though since they are marked rather hard.  BUT that doesn't mean you can't improve your writing and do well in the course.

He's nice to look at, and is a pretty engaging professor but he's a hard marker, I can't stress that enough, in another english course I was getting high 70s and low 80s and in his class I got 60s :/ No tests, all essays, and he shows no mercy. Pick another prof for ENG110 so that you can get a good mark.
He's without a doubt insane, but he makes the content very interesting. Attendance is mandatory, because he marks almost entirely on essays, and what he covers in class is perfect for essay material!

firstly I have no idea why he has such a high rating.  He is insane.  Absolutely insane, avoid him at ALL costs. Drop the class if you get him.  His expectations are crazy - he tells students with low marks to drop the class. He is very biased. And doesn't clarify anything on a test. + his essays are 2000 words for 12% of your mark in 2nd year.
Clever, funny guy. Seems a little obsessed with Native peoples of Canada, but whatever, it's his course to teach.

Amazing prof! Always available for help. Really friendly. Note that the poetry class is not for the feint of heart, and can be very difficult at times, but very rewarding. Also note: He's  cute. I mean, really, really cute.
very humourous, and engages participation
Cool guy, great prof

Excellent porfessor, and very passionate about teaching. Maintained control of the class without becoming condescending and taught with us rather than to us. Always available to help and very sexy. Course material varied and was often inter-active

I hated this course.It is a drama course prereq. and so it was filled with people who repeated themselves and talked constantly about how they "felt" about the readings. But my real problem with the course was he almost failed everyone by telling his TA to mark our first papers as a third year paper. WTF?!?! I dropped the course, take ENG 120!!
The fact that he just extended our final essay by a week gives him 100-friggin-% in my book. Awesome, awesome guy! Very fair, very approachable, and teaches a very rewarding class.
Brent Wood is the greatest professor ever! He's so easy to talk to and he's sweet too! I love him
He is a fun teacher and is extremely interactive and will help you if you need it. If you dont understand the readings, you will by the end of his class.

He is such a nice teacher...and easy to talk to. He makes the class more interactive that any other professor i kno...anywho...he to be a bit hyper...but he coo...y'all need to check that class. ...and get yourself an edumation.  One! (that means one love people, aye!)
Great teacher, he made my love for English come back. The overall class is great too, but you have to really enjoy reading.
